  <bioghist id="aspace_8b196de9e32b3e88d186ad4d7edfded2">
    <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
<p>E.A. Shaw &amp; Company, were cotton merchants and raw materials dealers with offices in Los Angeles and Boston.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_42c2afe2060747ba60b244b47fd01ab8">
    <head>Scope and Contents</head>
<p>Collection mostly from the Boston office and centering on information about ramie, a fiber obtained from the bark of the ramie plant. Includes correspondence, 1932-1933, 1948-1949, and 1954, all concerning ramie; some letters discuss decortication and degumming of the fibers. Also includes a file of information, 1956, about ramie; and folders of samples of ramie twine, including some made in Switzerland and tested by the Plymouth Cordage Co.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <custodhist id="aspace_df11b857846ee412924f7c8aed28da2b">
    <head>Custodial History</head>
<p>American Textile History Museum Collection, gift of Gordon Shaw.</p>  </custodhist>
